# MeetiA Site Update Rules

This folder is the public Astro site for MeetiA. Treat it as the publishing source connected to GitHub and Cloudflare Pages.

## Roles

- Obsidian / `My code`: knowledge base, writing rules, rough drafts, article ideas.
- `Meetia-site`: public website files, published blog Markdown, public images, site layout and styles.

When using Obsidian knowledge, read it as reference material, but save public website changes in this `Meetia-site` folder.

## Blog Articles

Published blog articles live in:

```txt
src/content/blog/
```

Use this template as the starting point:

```txt
src/content/blog/_template.md
```

Article frontmatter should follow this shape:

```md
---
title: "記事タイトル"
description: "読みもの一覧や検索結果に表示する短い説明文"
pubDate: 2026-05-06
draft: false
image: "/images/blog/example.webp"
---
```

- Use lowercase ASCII filenames with hyphens, such as `rainy-season-aroma-selfcare.md`.
- Set `draft: true` for drafts that should not be published.
- Set `draft: false` only when the article should appear on the public site.
- Keep each article focused on one theme when possible.
- Prefer a warm, conversational, readable tone for MeetiA readers.
- Use related links thoughtfully; avoid making readers loop without a clear next step.

## Blog Images

Blog images live in:

```txt
public/images/blog/
```

Use WebP for final blog images when possible.

Frontmatter image paths should look like:

```md
image: "/images/blog/example.webp"
```

Markdown body image paths should look like:

```md
![画像の説明](/images/blog/example.webp)
```

Do not leave website-referenced images outside `public/images/blog/`.

## Site Editing

Main places to edit:

```txt
src/content/blog/
public/images/blog/
src/pages/
src/styles/global.css
```

Avoid manual edits to generated or dependency folders:

```txt
.astro/
dist/
node_modules/
```

## Verification

Before publishing, run:

```sh
npm run build
```

For local preview during editing, use:

```sh
npm run dev
```

Cloudflare Pages settings:

```txt
Build command: npm run build
Build output directory: dist
Production branch: main
```

## Publishing

After changes are checked:

1. Save files.
2. Commit changes to `main`.
3. Push to GitHub.
4. Cloudflare Pages deploys automatically.

Use clear commit messages, for example:

```txt
Add rainy season aroma article
Update course page copy
```
